## Encoding Standard Reference

**Official Spec**: https://encoding.spec.whatwg.org/

**Project Files**:
- **`specs/encoding.md`** - Complete specification in markdown format (algorithms, encoding tables, implementation notes)
- **`specs/encoding.idl`** - WebIDL interface definitions (TextEncoder, TextDecoder, etc.)

**Key Sections** (in encoding.md):
- ¬ß1 Encodings - Character encoding definitions and labels
- ¬ß2 Encoding API - TextEncoder, TextDecoder interfaces
- ¬ß3 Names and labels - Encoding label resolution
- ¬ß4 Indexes - Encoding index tables for legacy encodings
- ¬ß5 Hooks - Extension points for HTML integration
- ¬ß6 Legacy encodings - Windows-1252, Big5, GBK, Shift_JIS, EUC-KR, etc.

**Key Interfaces** (in encoding.idl):
- `TextEncoder` - Encodes strings to UTF-8
- `TextDecoder` - Decodes byte streams to strings
- `TextEncoderStream` - Streaming UTF-8 encoder
- `TextDecoderStream` - Streaming decoder for any encoding

**Reading Guide**:
1. Start with `encoding.idl` for interface contracts and method signatures
2. Read `encoding.md` for algorithm implementations
3. Read all algorithm steps in order (don't skip)
4. Check encoding tables in ¬ß4 Indexes
5. Test against browser implementations when in doubt

